SIMPLE: outside
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outside
<hw>Out"side`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
external part of a thing; the part, end, or side which forms the
external surface; that which appears, or is manifest; that which is
superficial; the exterior.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There may be great need of an <qex>outside</qex> where there is
little or nothing within.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Created beings see nothing but our <qex>outside</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The part or space which lies beyond the external
edge of a structure or beyond the boundary of an inclosure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>I threw open the door of my chamber, and found the family standing
on the <qex>outside</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Spectator.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The furthest limit, as to number, quantity, extent,
etc.; the utmost; <as>as, it may last a week at the
<ex>outside</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>One who, or that which, is without; hence, an
<xex>outside</xex> passenger, as distinguished from one who is
<xex>inside</xex>. See <er>Inside</er>, <pos>n.</pos> 3.</def>
<mark>[Colloq. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>The part of the world not encompassed by or under
control of an organization or institution; <as>as, prisoners are not
allowed to pass objects to persons on the <ex>outside</ex>; one may not
discuss company secretes with anyone on the
<ex>outside</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outside</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Outside
<hw>Out"side`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to the outside; external; exterior; superficial.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Reaching the extreme or farthest limit, as to
extent, quantity, etc.; <as>as, an <ex>outside</ex> estimate</as>.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Outside finish</b></col> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>, <cd>a term
for the minor parts, as corner boards, hanging stiles, etc., required to
complete the exterior of a wooden building; -- rare in
masonry.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outside</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Outside
<hw>Out"side`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> or <pos>prep.</pos>
<def>On or to the outside (of); without; on the exterior; <as>as, to
ride <ex>outside</ex> the coach; he stayed
<ex>outside</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outsider</ent>⟦br⟧
